feature #300 [DBAL] Require QueryBuilder for generating (sstok)

This PR was merged into the main branch.
labels: bc-break

Discussion
----------

| Q             | A
| ------------- | ---
| Bug fix?      | no
| New feature?  | yes
| BC breaks?    | yes
| Deprecations? | 
| Tickets       | Closes #290 
| License       | MIT

Require a QueryBuilder is used for Doctrine DBAL, which also ensures ordering is applied correctly.
Due too some technical details it's no longer possible to retrieve the generated where-condition, this is now made all internal.

However I do plan to make a few test-helper classes to make testing of conversions much easier.

Commits
-------

30f46e816323f9d2876f973affb5713d38c690b3 Make CI work again

issue.title: [RFC][Feature][Doctrine] Require usage of the QueryBuilder
issue.body:
**Description**
In addition to #289 I propose to remove support for the Query object completely, and require the usage of a QueryBuilder only.

Note: It's still possible to get the generated Where condition and parameters.
But `updateQuery()` will only handle the usage of a QueryBuilder.
